The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 London, July 11 (PTI): A man and a woman, both of Indian origin, have been jailed following the discovery of more than 500 stolen goods at a house in Leicester, and face deportation to India.          
	The loot consist mainly of jewellery, mobile phones, cameras and other small electronic items that had been stolen in October and November 2009. Both will be deported to India at the end of their sentences, of 24 and 14 months.                  
	Dehri-on-Sone (PTI): Bihar police on Sunday arrested a person from a hotel here for allegedly duping railway job seekers out of lakhs of rupees and seized fake documents from him. A hunt has been launched to nab other members of the gang.                   
	Lucknow (PTI): Sixteen people have been arrested during raids by the Food and Drug Authority in 10 districts of Uttar Pradesh for unauthorised sale and use of oxytocin, a senior officer said. The raids were conducted on diaries, general stores and medical stores. Injecting cattle with oxytocin is banned under the Drugs and Cosmetic Act.                   
	Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A newlywed couple, who eloped and got married against the wishes of their parents, have sought police protection after the girls family allegedly threatened to kill them. The couple, both in their early 20s, had married on June 26.                  
	Coimbatore (PTI): The Centre will introduce a new seven-and-half-year ayurveda course, a senior official said. The curriculum will combine all the pre-ayurveda courses.                   
	Rameswaram (PTI): Fifty fishermen from Tamil Nadu were injured in an attack allegedly by Sri Lankan naval personnel while fishing off Katchathivu island on Sunday, fisheries department officials said.                                                                                                                                              
